<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>What causes LG dryers to make grinding noises?</h3>
<p>Grinding noises typically indicate worn drum rollers, damaged bearings, or debris caught in the blower housing. These components wear naturally over time, especially in units 4-7 years old.</p>
<h3>How long does LG dryer noise repair take?</h3>
<p>Most noise repairs take 45-90 minutes once we arrive on-site. Simple fixes like belt replacement are completed faster, while drum roller replacement requires more disassembly time.</p>
<h3>Should I continue using my LG dryer if it's making noise?</h3>
<p>Stop using your dryer immediately if you hear grinding, metal-on-metal scraping, or loud thumping sounds. Continued operation can cause expensive secondary damage to the drum or motor assembly.</p>
